questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a financial transaction service occasionally updates account balances incorrectly under high concurrent load. A junior engineer wrote the following class to update account balances, attempting to use a local cache flag to avoid redundant DB reads:

java
@Service
public class AccountService {
    private final AccountRepository repository;
    private boolean isCacheValid = false;

    public AccountService(AccountRepository repository) {
        this.repository = repository;
    }

    public void processPayment(Long accountId, BigDecimal amount) {
        if (!isCacheValid) {
            updateBalanceTx(accountId, amount);
            isCacheValid = true;
        }
    }

    @Transactional
    public void updateBalanceTx(Long accountId, BigDecimal amount) {
        Account account = repository.findById(accountId).orElseThrow();
        account.setBalance(account.getBalance().subtract(amount));
        repository.save(account);
    }
}


Under high concurrency, balances are updated incorrectly, and transactions do not appear to roll back on runtime exceptions.
